comment: Palhinhaea Franco & Vasc. is conserved against Lepidotis (@greuter20142292, @applequist2016report).

Paraphyletic in plastid [@du2022structural; @nitta2022open] and nuclear [@qi2018wellresolved; @shen2018largescale] phylogenomic analyses, but a vote to revise the treatment did not pass (<https://github.com/pteridogroup/ppg/issues/44>).
Paraphyletic [@vieiralima2023phylogenomic], but no name meeting the requirements of the Code is currently available (<https://github.com/pteridogroup/ppg/issues/78>).

Cheilanthes is more narrowly defined here than in most previous classifications. The bulk of the genus consists of a moderately supported clade within the hemionitids (@schuettpelz2025phylogenetically), but a few species treated in this genus are known to fall elsewhere in the cheilanthoid phylogeny (e.g., @kao2019lowcopy).
Was there a conservation of this name or something like that?
This wasn't monophyletic in PPGI but is now?
